title: For Sale:  1934 Czech VZ24 WWII 8mm mauser
postcontent: For sale is a warhorse of a rifle. A 1934 Czech VZ24 8mm mauser bolt action rifle. This rifle was made at the famous factory in Brno, Czech. It was sold to the Romanians who put their crest on it. The crest was partially scrubbed off by the Russians after the war. However a good part of it remains on the rifle, which is uncommon. The stock shows a lot of wear as you would expect from a rifle that saw action in 2 countries. The bore is dark in the grooves but has strong rifling. The Czech rifles were noted for their smooth actions and this one is no different. It cycles and fires with no problems. The upper hand guard has one small crack and one a little longer one that was repaired. Does not affect the function of the rifle. This rifle has a lot of history but has a lot of shooting life left in it. It would be good for the collector, a nice truck gun, hog gun, or deer rifle. The 8mm packs a punch. It comes with 20 rounds of surplus ammo. Asking $220, willing to negotiate a little. Please text any questions or requests for more pics to REDACTED. Thanks

title: For Sale/Trade:  Harrington & Richardson Topper 158 combo
postcontent: Up for sale or trade is the nicest break action H&R I've seen. Factory combo rifle / shotgun from the late 70s. It is an sb1 frame but of stronger construction that the standard. The rifle barrel and frame are factory fitted and bear the same serial number. There are no strength issues. Barrels swap with 1flathead screw. This particular one is in .30-30 win and 3" magnum 20ga. The rifle barrel has factory flip up rear sights with a factory scope mount included. Both barrels, the stocks, and the case colored reciever are all in excellent shape. Yes, I know what blue book is on this combo, and you try to find one for that. The rifle barrel is extremely accurate and a very handy length. The recoil pad is the factory hr pad and in great shape. Putting this up for sale or trade for something interesting. Ended up getting an old contender in .30-30 so I dont shoot this one as much any more. Really looking for a Ruger 10/22 with the full stock. Will consider all trade offers from glocks to contender barrels and everything else. I collect milsurps and old hunting rifles, figured if someone was interested in the topper I would give them a shot at it. I can add any amount of cash to a trade if I like it, lets make a deal.
